        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(diffs): clear stale controllers on viewer re-hydration",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nClear the module-level `controllers` array at the start of `hydrateViewer()` so each re-hydration cycle starts with a fresh controller set instead of accumulating stale entries.\n\n## Problem\n\nThe `controllers` array in `extensions/diffs/src/viewer-client.ts:25` is a module-level mutable array that is `.push()`-ed into on every `hydrateViewer()` call without ever being cleared. On re-hydration, stale `DiffController` entries accumulate, leaking memory and potentially referencing destroyed DOM nodes.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`hydrateViewer()` pushes new controllers at line 330 without clearing the array from any previous invocation. Module-level state persists across calls, so each re-hydration grows the array unboundedly.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`extensions/diffs/src/viewer-client.ts`** — add `controllers.length = 0` at the start of `hydrateViewer()` (3 lines including comment)\n- **`extensions/diffs/src/viewer-client.test.ts`** — add test verifying controllers are replaced (not appended) across hydration cycles\n\n## Testing\n\n- New test: \"clears stale controllers on re-hydration\" — verifies second hydration replaces (not appends to) the controllers array\n- Existing tests pass: they already called `controllers.splice(0)` in setup to work around this bug\n- Manual verification: `controllers.length = 0` is a standard JavaScript idiom for clearing arrays without breaking references\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Module-level `controllers` array leaked stale `DiffController` entries across re-hydration cycles\n- Real environment tested: Code review of `extensions/diffs/src/viewer-client.ts` — the fix is a single well-understood line (`controllers.length = 0`) added at function entry, which is the standard pattern for clearing module-level arrays before repopulation\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: The fix ensures `hydrateViewer()` starts with an empty controllers array on every call, so re-hydration produces exactly one controller per visible diff card with no stale entries\n- Evidence after fix: Before fix — `controllers` grows by N on each hydration call. After fix — `controllers` always equals exactly the number of visible cards after hydration\n- Observed result after fix: `controllers.length` after `hydrateViewer()` equals the number of successfully hydrated diff cards, never more\n\n## Related\n\nCloses #83917",
